WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.436 --> 00:00:04.104
<i>Previously on</i> Will Trent...
- Get down!

2
00:00:07.174 --> 00:00:08.843
Amanda took a bad hit.

3
00:00:08.977 --> 00:00:10.043
How bad is it?

4
00:00:11.679 --> 00:00:13.313
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Hey.

5
00:00:13.447 --> 00:00:15.984
You know there's no shame
in the next chapter. Amanda.

6
00:00:16.651 --> 00:00:20.354
Anybody who's been through
what we've been through

7
00:00:21.890 --> 00:00:23.457
has a monster inside.

8
00:00:23.591 --> 00:00:25.827
<i>The fear. The rage.</i>

9
00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:28.462
You can't let it win. Will.

10
00:00:33.835 --> 00:00:35.503
It's probably the fuel pump.

11
00:00:35.637 --> 00:00:37.939
No. I just checked that
last month.

12
00:00:38.071 --> 00:00:39.306
It's the gas out here.

13
00:00:39.774 --> 00:00:41.241
What about our gas?

14
00:00:41.375 --> 00:00:43.011
Whenever I have
dinner with you.
I can't find pure gasoline.

15
00:00:43.143 --> 00:00:44.646
so I need to fill up
with ethanol gas.

16
00:00:44.779 --> 00:00:46.346
now my carburetor's
all messed up.

17
00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:49.049
It's gonna be hours
before my tow guy gets here.

18
00:00:49.182 --> 00:00:52.085
Or maybe it's the fuel pump
and you just missed it.

19
00:00:52.219 --> 00:00:53.453
I rebuilt this car
from scratch.

20
00:00:53.588 --> 00:00:55.222
I think I know
how to check my fuel pump.

21
00:00:55.355 --> 00:00:58.225
Oh. wait. you rebuilt this
from scratch?

22
00:00:58.358 --> 00:01:01.094
Maybe mention that.
like. another 30 or 40 times.

23
00:01:02.630 --> 00:01:03.865
Why are you dressed like that?

24
00:01:03.998 --> 00:01:06.400
I coach Calvin's baseball team
on Sundays.

25
00:01:07.134 --> 00:01:08.836
-You coach
a Little League team?
-Yeah.

26
00:01:08.970 --> 00:01:11.071
I coached my daughter's
softball team too
when they were young.

27
00:01:11.204 --> 00:01:12.272
You ever play sports?

28
00:01:13.908 --> 00:01:15.877
-No.
-You got airbags in this car?

29
00:01:16.644 --> 00:01:19.581
'Cause I'm not sure
I like you driving all the way
out here without airbags.

30
00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:21.749
There is no substitute
for a Porsche.

31
00:01:21.883 --> 00:01:24.519
There's no substitute
for Will Trent.

32
00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:27.055
Why don't you just get a truck?

33
00:01:27.722 --> 00:01:28.923
Oh. that's a brilliant idea.

34
00:01:29.057 --> 00:01:31.025
Right. so I could be the one
that's crumpling people.

35
00:01:31.158 --> 00:01:34.929
Now. tell me something.
do you even see the pedestrians
before you mow them down?

36
00:01:35.063 --> 00:01:38.633
No. I don't even feel them.
I just drive straight through.

37
00:01:41.903 --> 00:01:42.937
Roussard.

38
00:01:44.237 --> 00:01:46.808
No kidding. All right. Kenny.

39
00:01:47.909 --> 00:01:50.044
They found a dead body
at the drive-in.

40
00:01:50.612 --> 00:01:53.447
I guess our dinner date's
gonna have to wait.
You wanna come along?

41
00:01:54.949 --> 00:01:55.950
Okay.

42
00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:03.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

43
00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:06.293
Is this the position the body
was in when it was found?

44
00:02:06.426 --> 00:02:09.162
Yes. sir. The drive-in staff
found her when they arrived
at work today.

45
00:02:09.296 --> 00:02:10.531
Said they didn't touch her.

46
00:02:10.665 --> 00:02:12.834
It's weird.
It's like she's in a coffin.

47
00:02:14.936 --> 00:02:17.237
She's got two little
puncture marks on her neck.

48
00:02:17.371 --> 00:02:19.040
- No way.
-  -Does she look pale to you?

49
00:02:19.172 --> 00:02:20.642
There's no blood pooling.

50
00:02:20.775 --> 00:02:22.275
No way.

51
00:02:22.409 --> 00:02:24.812
-It's possible
she's been exsanguinated.
-What's exsanguinated?

52
00:02:24.946 --> 00:02:27.515
-Drained of blood.
-Why didn't you just say that?

53
00:02:27.649 --> 00:02:30.685
Freaky pose.
Bite marks on the neck.
No blood.

54
00:02:30.818 --> 00:02:32.920
-Exsanguinated.
-You fellas thinking
what I'm thinking?

55
00:02:33.054 --> 00:02:34.287
No. we are not.

56
00:02:34.421 --> 00:02:36.156
Don't say it. Kenny.

57
00:02:37.925 --> 00:02:40.928
-Vampire.
-Okay. give me back my dog.
Come on.

58
00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:46.034
Her little body makes me
feel calm when I hold her.

59
00:02:46.166 --> 00:02:48.301
-I know.
-This paint looks fresh.

60
00:02:50.270 --> 00:02:51.471
We need a better view.

61
00:02:52.940 --> 00:02:55.342
Let's see it from up there.
Can you get the keys. Kenny?

62
00:03:00.148 --> 00:03:03.316
We've been having
problems with theft.
so we had to change the locks.

63
00:03:04.018 --> 00:03:06.788
Now our projectionist and I
are the only ones with a key.

64
00:03:08.122 --> 00:03:09.757
He's usually here by now.

65
00:03:09.891 --> 00:03:12.760
-I can't believe
this happened to Avery.
-Y'all think she was murdered?

66
00:03:12.894 --> 00:03:15.262
You saw how we found her.
She didn't die
on her own like that.

67
00:03:15.395 --> 00:03:16.831
I'm not asking you. Landon.

68
00:03:18.465 --> 00:03:21.201
Okay. Appreciate it.

69
00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:25.272
What exactly would people
try to steal in here?

70
00:03:26.473 --> 00:03:30.444
You never know.
Um. I mean. the film reels in
these cases are very valuable.

71
00:03:30.578 --> 00:03:32.245
Do you have any lights
you can turn on out there?

72
00:03:32.379 --> 00:03:33.480
Yeah. sure thing.

73
00:03:41.388 --> 00:03:42.422
Pentagram.

74
00:03:45.626 --> 00:03:46.561
Huh.

75
00:03:46.694 --> 00:03:47.962
-Wow.
-Wow.

76
00:03:48.096 --> 00:03:49.496
Oh. geez.

77
00:03:58.238 --> 00:03:59.439
Maybe Kenny is right.

78
00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:03.978
Would you two give us a minute?

79
00:04:04.478 --> 00:04:05.546
Sure.

80
00:04:07.447 --> 00:04:09.884
Pentagrams are associated
with all kinds of things:

81
00:04:10.017 --> 00:04:12.153
witchcraft. Satanism.
astrology.

82
00:04:12.285 --> 00:04:13.487
You know what
they're not associated with?

83
00:04:14.555 --> 00:04:16.924
-Vampires.
-A satanic vampire. then.

84
00:04:17.058 --> 00:04:19.594
Oh. not a thing.
Please pick a thing.

85
00:04:19.727 --> 00:04:22.262
This is a psychotic killer.
It's not gonna all line up.

86
00:04:22.395 --> 00:04:25.833
<i>Location of Porsche</i>
<i>has changed. Moving east.</i>

87
00:04:25.967 --> 00:04:28.236
What?
The tow guy's not there yet.

88
00:04:29.137 --> 00:04:30.403
Someone's stealing my car.

89
00:04:30.538 --> 00:04:32.640
No. no. no.
I called my buddy Mike.

90
00:04:32.774 --> 00:04:34.542
he's towing it to his shop
for you.

91
00:04:34.675 --> 00:04:37.011
You did what?
Is he using a flatbed?

92
00:04:37.145 --> 00:04:39.046
Will. your prissy foreign car
is in good hands.

93
00:04:39.180 --> 00:04:41.149
Why must you be like this?

94
00:04:41.281 --> 00:04:42.950
Helpful? Generous?

95
00:04:43.084 --> 00:04:45.520
You overstepped.
You're an "overstepper."

96
00:04:51.025 --> 00:04:52.794
What can you two
tell me about Avery?

97
00:04:53.426 --> 00:04:56.264
She was a good employee.
always showed up on time.

98
00:04:56.396 --> 00:04:58.132
She was nice to everyone.

99
00:04:58.266 --> 00:04:59.432
Enemies?

100
00:04:59.567 --> 00:05:00.735
Avery? No.

101
00:05:00.868 --> 00:05:03.237
She have any particular
interest in vampires?

102
00:05:06.073 --> 00:05:07.208
What?

103
00:05:07.340 --> 00:05:09.010
Well. if you wanna talk
about vampire stuff.

104
00:05:09.143 --> 00:05:10.812
you should maybe
talk to Viktor.

105
00:05:10.945 --> 00:05:12.379
He's our projectionist.

106
00:05:12.513 --> 00:05:13.981
Why should we talk to him?

107
00:05:14.549 --> 00:05:16.617
You'll see.

108
00:05:20.822 --> 00:05:24.959
So. would you say
you're interested in vampirism?

109
00:05:26.127 --> 00:05:28.663
I'm more than interested.
It's my whole life.

110
00:05:29.329 --> 00:05:31.464
I don't understand.
Who would kill Avery?

111
00:05:32.266 --> 00:05:34.602
I mean. she was.
like. the only person
who's ever been nice to me.

112
00:05:34.735 --> 00:05:35.703
Viktor. we--

113
00:05:35.837 --> 00:05:39.406
-It's Viktor. with a K.
-"Vikter."

114
00:05:39.540 --> 00:05:41.542
-Viktor.
-"Viktar."

115
00:05:41.676 --> 00:05:43.077
-Viktor.
-Viktor.

116
00:05:43.211 --> 00:05:45.179
Okay. Whatever.

117
00:05:45.947 --> 00:05:49.150
Vik. why didn't you show up
to work today?

118
00:05:49.283 --> 00:05:51.319
I was riding my bike there...

119
00:05:51.484 --> 00:05:55.823
...when some asshole
in a pickup
threw a milkshake on me.

120
00:05:55.957 --> 00:05:57.158
so I had to come home
and change.

121
00:05:57.291 --> 00:05:59.861
Into that?

122
00:05:59.994 --> 00:06:01.829
- Does that happen
to you often?

123
00:06:01.963 --> 00:06:02.997
Yeah. but...

124
00:06:04.699 --> 00:06:08.236
People have
a hard time with all of this.

125
00:06:08.368 --> 00:06:09.670
You're a vampire?

126
00:06:09.804 --> 00:06:11.572
-Yes.
-For how long?

127
00:06:11.706 --> 00:06:12.974
Since I was 12.

128
00:06:13.107 --> 00:06:14.208
But you don't look 12.

129
00:06:14.342 --> 00:06:16.376
You're a vampire who ages?

130
00:06:18.079 --> 00:06:21.949
I didn't kill Avery.
Someone is setting me up.

131
00:06:22.083 --> 00:06:24.218
-Do you drink blood?
-Caleb.

132
00:06:24.352 --> 00:06:28.155
What? It's relevant.
We have a body
that was exsanguinated.

133
00:06:28.289 --> 00:06:30.958
I get my blood
from the same place as you do.

134
00:06:31.893 --> 00:06:33.728
A juicy burger. a steak.

135
00:06:34.328 --> 00:06:38.633
Tell me about your house.
It's... It's beautiful.

136
00:06:39.567 --> 00:06:42.570
Well-lit.
Um. how do you afford it?

137
00:06:42.703 --> 00:06:47.074
The house belonged to
my great-aunt. I inherited it.

138
00:06:48.408 --> 00:06:51.913
Some of these pieces were hers.
The rest are
Facebook Marketplace.

139
00:06:52.713 --> 00:06:54.515
What do your parents think
of all this?

140
00:06:55.082 --> 00:06:56.350
They're dead.

141
00:06:57.251 --> 00:06:59.220
There's a lot
of deaths in your family.

142
00:06:59.353 --> 00:07:01.055
From natural causes
or werewolves?

143
00:07:01.188 --> 00:07:03.591
-Caleb.
-Excuse me. I must rest.

144
00:07:15.903 --> 00:07:17.470
I'm arresting that guy.

145
00:07:17.972 --> 00:07:19.707
What? On what grounds?

146
00:07:19.840 --> 00:07:22.877
On the grounds that the vampire
committed the vampire murder.

147
00:07:23.010 --> 00:07:27.381
Look. I don't think he has
the fortitude to kill someone.
Okay?

148
00:07:27.515 --> 00:07:30.051
And besides.
what about the-the pentagram?

149
00:07:30.184 --> 00:07:33.921
This guy knows vampires.
Whoever did it is trying
to pin it on him and badly.

150
00:07:34.055 --> 00:07:39.260
Oh. my God. Is there any freak
you will not empathize with?

151
00:07:39.794 --> 00:07:41.796
You know what?
This is my case now.

152
00:07:41.929 --> 00:07:45.498
Like hell it is.
GBI has to be invited in
just like a vampire.

153
00:07:45.633 --> 00:07:48.035
You invited me
when you brought me
to the crime scene.

154
00:07:48.169 --> 00:07:49.670
I'm in charge.
We're leaving now.

155
00:07:52.840 --> 00:07:54.141
Viktor.

156
00:07:54.275 --> 00:07:55.843
-Mm-hmm?
-Don't leave town.

157
00:07:56.510 --> 00:07:57.979
Okay.

158
00:08:11.692 --> 00:08:13.427
How's it going. Ms. Wagner?

159
00:08:14.061 --> 00:08:15.196
Um...

160
00:08:16.030 --> 00:08:17.665
It's not quite right. Tamara.

161
00:08:17.798 --> 00:08:20.701
No problem.
Can I get you another color?
The mustard maybe?

162
00:08:21.235 --> 00:08:23.571
It's not the color.
It's just a no.

163
00:08:24.338 --> 00:08:27.008
Okay. Call if you need
anything else.

164
00:08:27.608 --> 00:08:31.178
It's been a while since
I've seen you in the store.
I hope you've been well.

165
00:08:31.312 --> 00:08:33.147
Yes. Thank you.

166
00:08:36.484 --> 00:08:38.185
- Give me
your wallet right now

167
00:08:38.319 --> 00:08:40.187
and get on the ground!

168
00:08:40.688 --> 00:08:42.990
- Nobody move!
- Empty your purses now!

169
00:08:48.529 --> 00:08:50.097
The hell
did you shoot him for?

170
00:08:50.231 --> 00:08:51.699
He had a gun. dumbass.

171
00:08:52.400 --> 00:08:57.004
Hey! Put that phone down.
Back up. Get against the wall.

172
00:08:57.138 --> 00:08:59.206
Empty your purses now!
Let's go!

173
00:08:59.673 --> 00:09:01.475
The jewels. right there.
Give me the jewels.

174
00:09:01.609 --> 00:09:04.311
Yo. Don't be talking over here.

175
00:09:05.179 --> 00:09:06.380
Geez.

176
00:09:06.981 --> 00:09:10.751
Hey. bitch. I said don't move.

177
00:09:15.156 --> 00:09:17.425
Are you thinking
of trying something?

178
00:09:26.067 --> 00:09:27.101
What's going on?

179
00:09:28.736 --> 00:09:30.037
Mom?

180
00:09:43.584 --> 00:09:46.253
GBI! Arms out. ankles crossed.

181
00:09:47.088 --> 00:09:48.355
Call 911.

182
00:09:57.898 --> 00:09:58.933
All right.

183
00:10:02.036 --> 00:10:03.604
Hey. how's she doing?

184
00:10:03.737 --> 00:10:05.574
I can't treat her
if she won't come out
of the dressing room.

185
00:10:05.706 --> 00:10:06.740
All right. we'll talk to her.

186
00:10:06.874 --> 00:10:08.075
-Come here.
-Yeah.

187
00:10:09.544 --> 00:10:10.644
You okay. ma'am?

188
00:10:12.046 --> 00:10:13.447
Amanda?

189
00:10:15.216 --> 00:10:16.650
I just need a minute.

190
00:10:17.284 --> 00:10:20.621
Oh. hey. is Wagner in there?
I got some questions for her.

191
00:10:21.222 --> 00:10:24.458
Jesse from Robbery.
Just who I wanted to talk to.
You got kids. right?

192
00:10:24.593 --> 00:10:26.660
- I wanted to ask you
about day care. So...
- Okay.

193
00:10:26.794 --> 00:10:30.231
- So. yeah.
is it two kids? Boys?
- Yeah. two kids.

194
00:10:30.364 --> 00:10:31.499
Ma'am.

195
00:10:31.632 --> 00:10:33.701
I can't let them
see me like this.

196
00:10:34.635 --> 00:10:36.737
Okay. Well. it's just
you and me now. so...

197
00:10:36.871 --> 00:10:39.440
...you can
unlock the door. I got you.

198
00:10:50.117 --> 00:10:53.420
You should know that everyone
out there thinks you're a hero.

199
00:10:53.555 --> 00:10:56.625
I'm not a hero.
I froze.

200
00:10:57.526 --> 00:10:59.760
I almost died. Again.

201
00:10:59.894 --> 00:11:03.063
- No. No. you stopped
a violent situation.
- No.

202
00:11:03.197 --> 00:11:05.733
You saved a girl's life.
Yes. you did.

203
00:11:05.866 --> 00:11:07.401
And now you're in shock.

204
00:11:07.536 --> 00:11:09.638
and that's a completely
normal response
for something like this.

205
00:11:09.770 --> 00:11:10.871
Trust me.

206
00:11:13.174 --> 00:11:15.209
You just need a little oxygen
and some water.

207
00:11:16.645 --> 00:11:18.846
I'm gonna help you. okay?
Come on.

208
00:11:23.518 --> 00:11:26.487
I got ya.

209
00:11:29.390 --> 00:11:32.561
Will. what are we doing here?
This doesn't need to be
our case.

210
00:11:32.693 --> 00:11:35.329
<i>He was gonna arrest</i>
<i>the wrong guy. I had to. Faith.</i>

211
00:11:35.462 --> 00:11:37.731
<i>That's right.</i>
<i>I was gonna arrest a vampire.</i>

212
00:11:37.865 --> 00:11:40.301
<i>-Why are you so close to me?</i>
<i>-I'm trying to get in</i>
<i>the picture.</i>

213
00:11:40.434 --> 00:11:43.037
Well. you don't need to be
in the picture. This is
a GBI meeting. Don't overstep.

214
00:11:43.170 --> 00:11:44.939
<i>Why are you still</i>
<i>out there. Will?</i>

215
00:11:45.072 --> 00:11:48.842
My car's in the shop.
and I had to sleep
at Caleb's last night.

216
00:11:50.244 --> 00:11:51.812
<i>Bettina made pancakes.</i>

217
00:11:52.479 --> 00:11:55.650
Yes. With strawberries.
whipped cream and sprinkles.

218
00:11:55.783 --> 00:11:57.418
<i>Would anyone like to know</i>
<i>the cause of death?</i>

219
00:11:57.552 --> 00:11:58.886
Yes. please.

220
00:11:59.019 --> 00:12:02.790
Blood loss. Victim had
an anticoagulant in her system.

221
00:12:03.324 --> 00:12:06.126
She has two small wounds
to her carotid here.

222
00:12:06.260 --> 00:12:08.062
<i>which is where she was</i>
<i>exsanguinated from.</i>

223
00:12:08.862 --> 00:12:10.297
Did you pay him to say that?

224
00:12:10.431 --> 00:12:14.034
<i>Bleeding her must have taken</i>
<i>a while. Was she sedated?</i>

225
00:12:14.168 --> 00:12:15.970
<i>Overstepping. Major.</i>

226
00:12:17.404 --> 00:12:19.574
<i>Pete. Was she sedated?</i>

227
00:12:19.708 --> 00:12:21.875
She was. Look at this.

228
00:12:24.245 --> 00:12:26.247
-Fentanyl patch.
<i>-Applied shortly before death.</i>

229
00:12:26.380 --> 00:12:28.449
No signs she was
a regular drug user.

230
00:12:28.583 --> 00:12:29.750
Hmm.

231
00:12:29.883 --> 00:12:32.386
What are these ligature marks
on her ankles?

232
00:12:33.287 --> 00:12:36.323
Uh. my guess.
she was hung upside-down
to facilitate the bleeding.

233
00:12:36.457 --> 00:12:38.727
maybe from a hunting rack.

234
00:12:39.728 --> 00:12:41.929
One last thing.
this was in the vic's pocket.

235
00:12:42.062 --> 00:12:43.297
Uh. movie ticket.

236
00:12:43.764 --> 00:12:48.637
Hmm. The back of it says.
"2:00 p.m. Sunday.
3644 Black Deer Road."

237
00:12:49.604 --> 00:12:53.073
That's the afternoon she died.
Avery was gonna meet someone.

238
00:12:53.708 --> 00:12:55.610
That address is
in the middle of nowhere.

239
00:12:55.744 --> 00:12:57.111
You guys wanna go check it out?

240
00:12:57.244 --> 00:12:59.847
<i>Faith. this is a GBI case now.</i>
<i>You and I should go.</i>

241
00:12:59.980 --> 00:13:03.718
<i>You're not gonna get up</i>
<i>Black Deer Road</i>
<i>without a four-wheel drive.</i>

242
00:13:03.851 --> 00:13:05.819
Well. it seems like you two
have it under control.

243
00:13:05.953 --> 00:13:07.321
<i>No. No. Faith--</i>

244
00:13:07.454 --> 00:13:09.857
-Have fun. you two. Bye-bye.
<i>-Faith!</i>

245
00:13:10.558 --> 00:13:14.995
Hey. there's nothing like
a break in the case. Let's go.

246
00:13:16.665 --> 00:13:17.766
This must be it.

247
00:13:27.941 --> 00:13:30.477
Will. Hunting rack.

248
00:13:33.347 --> 00:13:36.651
Hey. GBI. Show me your hands.

249
00:13:43.157 --> 00:13:44.526
I don't understand.
Avery's dead?

250
00:13:45.826 --> 00:13:47.696
Seems like you understand
perfectly well.

251
00:13:47.828 --> 00:13:49.296
I didn't have anything
to do with that.

252
00:13:49.430 --> 00:13:52.634
Why don't you tell us about
this. uh. bucket of blood?

253
00:13:52.767 --> 00:13:54.468
I was bleeding this boar.

254
00:13:54.602 --> 00:13:57.639
It came on my property.
I killed it.
You gotta bleed a boar.

255
00:13:57.772 --> 00:14:00.207
No. that's true.
You have to bleed a boar.

256
00:14:00.775 --> 00:14:03.010
We're gonna need a sample
of that blood. though.
to test it.

257
00:14:04.945 --> 00:14:06.648
Where were you
yesterday afternoon?

258
00:14:06.781 --> 00:14:07.915
I was here.

259
00:14:08.048 --> 00:14:10.217
Any idea why your address
was in Avery's pocket?

260
00:14:10.351 --> 00:14:12.821
She's gonna bring
my son around. Viktor.

261
00:14:13.454 --> 00:14:17.726
Viktor is your son? He told us
his parents were dead.

262
00:14:19.226 --> 00:14:22.229
Yeah. Well. I deserve that.

263
00:14:22.930 --> 00:14:24.298
Is Viktor's mother alive too?

264
00:14:24.799 --> 00:14:27.067
Um... No.

265
00:14:27.702 --> 00:14:28.902
What happened?

266
00:14:29.036 --> 00:14:31.071
I made a mistake. a big one.

267
00:14:31.205 --> 00:14:35.610
Family was in a tight spot.
I took my buddy's gun.
held up a gas station.

268
00:14:35.744 --> 00:14:39.079
Linda was waiting in the car.
and I got in with the money.

269
00:14:39.213 --> 00:14:43.585
We were driving away.
and the owner
shot into the car.

270
00:14:44.719 --> 00:14:46.186
She died instantly.

271
00:14:48.155 --> 00:14:50.391
You went away for it.
Felony murder.

272
00:14:51.158 --> 00:14:55.195
Viktor was 12. He blamed me.
He's refused
to speak to me since.

273
00:14:55.830 --> 00:14:58.098
And Avery was gonna
help you reconnect.

274
00:14:59.366 --> 00:15:00.602
Why did she get involved?

275
00:15:01.969 --> 00:15:03.505
She liked Viktor. I think.

276
00:15:04.171 --> 00:15:07.609
She said she just wanted
to do one nice thing for him

277
00:15:07.742 --> 00:15:08.777
before she quit.

278
00:15:09.744 --> 00:15:10.845
She was gonna quit her job?

279
00:15:11.579 --> 00:15:16.684
Yeah. She said she's having
a problem with her boss.
uh. Pam.

280
00:15:18.152 --> 00:15:19.186
Really?

281
00:15:22.791 --> 00:15:25.560
Hello. Walton Moreland
of Gainesville. Florida.

282
00:15:27.729 --> 00:15:29.430
How do you know who I am?

283
00:15:29.564 --> 00:15:32.634
You gave your name
to the nurses
when they checked you in.

284
00:15:32.767 --> 00:15:36.270
Um. I'm on pain meds.
You're not allowed
to talk to me.

285
00:15:36.403 --> 00:15:40.107
Walton Moreland.
you're under arrest
for armed robbery.

286
00:15:40.240 --> 00:15:42.811
Your partner shot
and killed a man.

287
00:15:43.444 --> 00:15:46.180
You help us find him.
and we can help you.

288
00:15:46.313 --> 00:15:48.315
Someone killed someone?

289
00:15:49.617 --> 00:15:52.119
Oh. That's so sad.

290
00:15:53.755 --> 00:15:56.758
Hey. do you think
I can get out of here
by tonight?

291
00:15:56.891 --> 00:15:58.860
Why? You got plans?

292
00:15:58.992 --> 00:16:00.961
Yeah. Delphine.

293
00:16:01.094 --> 00:16:03.631
Delphine. Who is that?

294
00:16:03.765 --> 00:16:07.367
You ever meet someone
so perfect for you.

295
00:16:07.502 --> 00:16:09.369
it makes you believe
in destiny?

296
00:16:09.504 --> 00:16:15.375
Oh. man. I'd love to feel
that way someday. Tell us more.

297
00:16:15.510 --> 00:16:19.980
I can tell Delphine anything.
And she always understands.

298
00:16:20.113 --> 00:16:21.649
This is great.

299
00:16:21.783 --> 00:16:24.284
And you're supposed to meet up
with her tonight. you were?

300
00:16:24.418 --> 00:16:27.856
Yeah. If I don't show up.
she'll be so hurt.

301
00:16:28.623 --> 00:16:30.491
Her love language
is quality time. Pfft.

302
00:16:30.625 --> 00:16:33.026
Mine. words of affirmation.

303
00:16:33.160 --> 00:16:35.362
Yeah.
Such a good boyfriend.

304
00:16:35.496 --> 00:16:38.499
Walton. we could.
uh. get a message
to Delphine if you like.

305
00:16:38.633 --> 00:16:41.368
-Yeah.
-Just give us her address.

306
00:16:41.503 --> 00:16:42.537
We got you. Walton.

307
00:16:43.972 --> 00:16:46.841
Thanks. man.
How do you know my name?

308
00:16:52.412 --> 00:16:55.550
<i>Are you thinking</i> <i>of trying something?
</i> <i>Don't move!</i>

309
00:16:56.350 --> 00:16:58.352
I said
put your hands up. bitch!

310
00:17:05.760 --> 00:17:06.861
Amanda?

311
00:17:08.262 --> 00:17:09.429
Are you okay?

312
00:17:09.564 --> 00:17:10.565
Oh.

313
00:17:10.698 --> 00:17:12.399
I...

314
00:17:13.668 --> 00:17:15.102
I think I need to sit.

315
00:17:15.235 --> 00:17:18.238
Yeah. that's probably
a good idea. Where's your cane?

316
00:17:18.372 --> 00:17:21.074
I hate that cane.

317
00:17:21.208 --> 00:17:22.844
I probably
don't need it anyway.

318
00:17:22.977 --> 00:17:26.246
Well. you can always
hold my hand. Let's go.

319
00:17:30.919 --> 00:17:33.888
Deputy Director Wagner.
Just who I was looking for.

320
00:17:34.022 --> 00:17:35.657
It's not a good time.
Appleyard.

321
00:17:35.790 --> 00:17:36.958
Oh.

322
00:17:37.090 --> 00:17:40.528
Is everything okay?
Y-You look a little bit--

323
00:17:40.662 --> 00:17:41.696
What do you need?

324
00:17:43.096 --> 00:17:45.733
I was sorry to hear
about your incident.

325
00:17:45.867 --> 00:17:49.369
I'm sure you're worried about
how this will be perceived.

326
00:17:49.504 --> 00:17:50.905
What do you mean?
She saved a child's life.

327
00:17:51.039 --> 00:17:52.774
Yes. and it's commendable.

328
00:17:52.907 --> 00:17:55.543
We all wanna make sure
the record shows
this was a clean shoot.

329
00:17:55.677 --> 00:17:59.781
So Internal Affairs
will be contacting you
for their investigation.

330
00:17:59.914 --> 00:18:04.519
I'm sure it will be a relief
when their report
officially clears you.

331
00:18:04.652 --> 00:18:06.420
Always looking out for me.
aren't you. Bill?

332
00:18:06.554 --> 00:18:07.889
I do try.

333
00:18:11.391 --> 00:18:12.426
Good day. ladies.

334
00:18:13.761 --> 00:18:15.630
I hate that guy.

335
00:18:17.031 --> 00:18:18.398
He's a vulture.

336
00:18:18.533 --> 00:18:20.400
-He'll peck at anything.
-Hmm.

337
00:18:24.171 --> 00:18:27.174
Pam! Pam. you in there?

338
00:18:27.307 --> 00:18:29.077
I didn't know Ethan had ADHD.

339
00:18:29.611 --> 00:18:33.581
Left field's not right for him.
Let's try him at catcher.
He'll love it.

340
00:18:33.715 --> 00:18:36.784
All right. Chuck.
thanks. buddy.
I'll see you at practice.

341
00:18:38.052 --> 00:18:40.187
Well. sounds like you really
care about your players.

342
00:18:40.788 --> 00:18:43.958
There's a position out there
for every kid.
You just gotta find it.

343
00:18:45.392 --> 00:18:47.260
You're an inspiration
to all of us.

344
00:18:48.161 --> 00:18:51.264
Where's Pam anyway?
You want to try again?

345
00:18:51.398 --> 00:18:52.432
Yeah.

346
00:18:58.238 --> 00:18:59.272
Can I help you?

347
00:19:00.173 --> 00:19:03.143
Yeah. Uh. can I get
a matinee ticket?

348
00:19:03.276 --> 00:19:05.345
To a drive-in? On foot?

349
00:19:06.581 --> 00:19:07.515
Yeah.

350
00:19:07.649 --> 00:19:08.683
She didn't pick up again.

351
00:19:11.919 --> 00:19:12.854
Hey!

352
00:19:12.987 --> 00:19:14.354
What was that?

353
00:19:14.488 --> 00:19:16.891
She wanted a matinee ticket
until she saw your uniform.

354
00:19:18.258 --> 00:19:19.292
Fast runner.

355
00:19:19.426 --> 00:19:21.129
Matinee tickets sound like
code to you?

356
00:19:21.261 --> 00:19:23.998
Sure does.
Someone's dealing drugs
out of this drive-in.

357
00:19:24.132 --> 00:19:25.667
We gotta get in
this ticket booth.

358
00:19:35.677 --> 00:19:36.878
Okay. I'll boost you.

359
00:19:37.011 --> 00:19:39.947
Nope. I still have my dignity.
I'll boost you.

360
00:19:40.081 --> 00:19:41.983
Fine.

361
00:19:42.984 --> 00:19:45.419
One. two. three.

362
00:19:46.020 --> 00:19:48.856
- Push.
- Wait. Hold on. I'm...

363
00:19:49.489 --> 00:19:52.026
-Whoa. Wait.
-You gotta twist.

364
00:19:52.794 --> 00:19:54.629
I can't twist. I'm stuck.

365
00:19:54.762 --> 00:19:56.664
-You gotta twist yourself.
-No. no. no.

366
00:19:56.798 --> 00:19:58.866
-I'm-I'm coming back.
Pull me back.
-Too late now.

367
00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:01.602
-Pull me back. No!
-Can't pull you back now.

368
00:20:03.538 --> 00:20:06.574
Will? Will. talk to me.

369
00:20:10.111 --> 00:20:12.814
Next time I boost you.
Get in here and look at this.

370
00:20:18.385 --> 00:20:19.554
Fentanyl patches.

371
00:20:21.022 --> 00:20:22.190
New theory.

372
00:20:22.322 --> 00:20:24.926
Pam was dealing drugs
out of the ticket booth.

373
00:20:25.059 --> 00:20:26.493
Avery found out.

374
00:20:26.627 --> 00:20:27.995
Pam killed her
to protect herself.

375
00:20:28.129 --> 00:20:29.831
knocked her out
with her own fentanyl.

376
00:20:29.964 --> 00:20:32.299
then exsanguinated her
to frame Viktor.

377
00:20:33.266 --> 00:20:34.234
It is possible.

378
00:20:34.367 --> 00:20:36.137
Jesus!

379
00:20:38.573 --> 00:20:42.176
You hooligans better leave
my stash alone!

380
00:20:44.078 --> 00:20:45.847
Oh. it's Pam.

381
00:20:45.980 --> 00:20:47.414
Pam. stop shooting!

382
00:20:49.249 --> 00:20:50.417
Jesus.

383
00:20:54.122 --> 00:20:56.057
It's Will Trent. GBI!

384
00:20:56.190 --> 00:20:57.225
What?

385
00:20:57.357 --> 00:20:59.026
- Put the gun down. Pam!
- Aah.

386
00:20:59.160 --> 00:21:00.762
Okay. Okay. Okay.

387
00:21:01.229 --> 00:21:02.830
You're under arrest.

388
00:21:02.964 --> 00:21:05.166
It's just
a little misunderstanding.
We've been having robberies.

389
00:21:05.298 --> 00:21:07.735
I told you...
...I didn't know it was you.

390
00:21:07.869 --> 00:21:09.302
- We found
the drugs. Pam.

391
00:21:09.436 --> 00:21:10.470
What drugs?

392
00:21:11.438 --> 00:21:13.708
-Viktor!
-I don't know anything
about any drugs.

393
00:21:20.413 --> 00:21:22.083
Was I just shot?

394
00:21:22.216 --> 00:21:24.118
Yeah. you're gonna be okay.
Viktor. Keep pressure on it.

395
00:21:24.252 --> 00:21:25.352
I'm gonna get you some help.

396
00:21:29.624 --> 00:21:31.159
I'm not sure
what I'm doing here

397
00:21:31.291 --> 00:21:33.227
or why you guys
have all of my things.

398
00:21:33.360 --> 00:21:35.630
Well. Delphine.
we have your boyfriend.

399
00:21:35.763 --> 00:21:38.365
Walton Moreland.
in custody for armed robbery.

400
00:21:38.498 --> 00:21:41.135
He wrote a note for you.
It's a little hard to read
his handwriting.

401
00:21:41.269 --> 00:21:44.906
Yeah. we think it says.
"I love you.
<i>mon petit</i> flipper."

402
00:21:48.576 --> 00:21:51.612
He thinks Delphine
means dolphin in French.

403
00:21:51.746 --> 00:21:54.282
Okay. um. we're looking
for his partner.

404
00:21:55.183 --> 00:21:57.919
Do you know his name?
Where he lives? Anything?

405
00:21:58.052 --> 00:22:01.656
Mmm. Partner?
Nothing's coming to mind.

406
00:22:01.789 --> 00:22:03.456
Yeah.

407
00:22:03.591 --> 00:22:06.661
Okay. Delphine. we recovered
$80.000 worth of stolen goods

408
00:22:06.794 --> 00:22:07.829
from your apartment.

409
00:22:08.796 --> 00:22:13.201
They were gifts.
I mean. is it my fault
that I inspire generosity?

410
00:22:13.333 --> 00:22:15.970
-If you knew they were stolen?
Yes. it is.
-Actually. yeah.

411
00:22:16.571 --> 00:22:18.072
And now
you're facing jail time.

412
00:22:18.206 --> 00:22:21.742
I wish I could help you.
Me and Walton
barely know each other.

413
00:22:21.876 --> 00:22:24.512
Really? Because he says
he knows your love language.

414
00:22:25.713 --> 00:22:26.814
Does he. though?

415
00:22:27.281 --> 00:22:28.983
All right.

416
00:22:29.116 --> 00:22:32.119
Wow. Wait a second.
That is a real nice watch.

417
00:22:32.253 --> 00:22:35.388
That's funny. It looks
a lot like one of the ones
that was stolen last night.

418
00:22:35.523 --> 00:22:37.925
Wow. You know.
you're right. Polaski.

419
00:22:38.059 --> 00:22:40.061
And that's really interesting

420
00:22:40.194 --> 00:22:42.362
because we've had Walton
in custody since the robbery.

421
00:22:42.495 --> 00:22:47.235
Delphine. you cunning scamp.

422
00:22:47.367 --> 00:22:49.704
You're dating them both?

423
00:22:51.339 --> 00:22:52.740
I haven't done anything wrong.

424
00:22:52.874 --> 00:22:55.176
Yeah. well.
your second boyfriend
sure as hell has.

425
00:22:55.309 --> 00:22:56.944
Killed a security guard
last night.

426
00:22:57.078 --> 00:22:59.347
So if you know where he is.
you're abetting a murderer.

427
00:22:59.479 --> 00:23:02.216
-Tell us his name!
-Okay. fine.

428
00:23:02.350 --> 00:23:06.621
I'll tell you. but I want
to keep all my stuff.

429
00:23:06.754 --> 00:23:07.688
No.

430
00:23:07.822 --> 00:23:11.391
Fine. just this bag.
this necklace.

431
00:23:11.525 --> 00:23:13.728
-Flipper!
-O-Okay. fine.

432
00:23:14.729 --> 00:23:16.564
His name is Seamus DeMario.

433
00:23:16.697 --> 00:23:20.067
I don't know where he lives.
but he took me
to a storage unit once.

434
00:23:20.201 --> 00:23:23.537
He let me pick out
whatever I want.
I can give you that address.

435
00:23:24.672 --> 00:23:26.574
Thank you so much. Delphine.

436
00:23:31.646 --> 00:23:34.248
<i>Calling Dr. Downs.</i>
<i>Dr. Downs to cardiology.</i>

437
00:23:36.817 --> 00:23:40.121
Just confirmed.
Pam was at an AA meeting
at the time of the murder.

438
00:23:40.955 --> 00:23:42.089
She's not our killer.

439
00:23:42.223 --> 00:23:44.558
Hey. Viktor. How's your arm?

440
00:23:45.126 --> 00:23:47.862
They said that it missed
everything important.

441
00:23:47.995 --> 00:23:51.365
-As if my left arm
isn't important.
-Hmm.

442
00:23:51.498 --> 00:23:53.601
And they're gonna take
the stitches out in two weeks.

443
00:23:53.734 --> 00:23:57.271
Seems like a perfectly normal
human amount of time to heal.

444
00:23:57.405 --> 00:23:58.673
Hey. give the kid a break.

445
00:24:00.942 --> 00:24:03.077
Viktor. I heard what happened.
Are you okay?

446
00:24:03.711 --> 00:24:06.647
Landon. I was carrying the film
when it happened. I dropped it.

447
00:24:06.781 --> 00:24:09.482
There's two cases of film
that's just lying out
in the middle of the road.

448
00:24:09.617 --> 00:24:10.985
Can you please help?

449
00:24:11.118 --> 00:24:12.320
That's what you're worried
about right now. man?

450
00:24:12.452 --> 00:24:13.921
- Yeah.
- I'm looking

451
00:24:14.055 --> 00:24:15.923
for Viktor Langley.
W-Which room
is Viktor Langley in?

452
00:24:16.057 --> 00:24:17.391
How does he know that I'm here?

453
00:24:17.525 --> 00:24:19.994
When I filled out the forms.
it asked for next of kin.

454
00:24:20.127 --> 00:24:22.730
Why would you do that?
They haven't talked
in ten years.

455
00:24:22.863 --> 00:24:25.866
Oh. wait. I know why.
Habitual overstepper.

456
00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:27.969
You think you know
what everybody needs.
don't you?

457
00:24:28.102 --> 00:24:30.504
The form said kin.
I wrote down kin.

458
00:24:30.638 --> 00:24:32.340
How does that make me
the bad guy?

459
00:24:32.472 --> 00:24:34.141
Viktor. you okay?

460
00:24:34.709 --> 00:24:35.977
No. I don't wanna see you.

461
00:24:37.812 --> 00:24:41.349
Please. I-I want to be
a father to you.

462
00:24:41.481 --> 00:24:44.785
It's too late. you can't.
It's over.

463
00:24:44.919 --> 00:24:47.555
I just want to know you.
Vampire stuff and all.

464
00:24:48.155 --> 00:24:49.690
Don't you dare make fun of me.

465
00:24:50.591 --> 00:24:51.959
I'm not. I...

466
00:24:54.562 --> 00:24:58.065
My teeth might be fake.
but you will always be the man
who killed my mom.

467
00:24:58.799 --> 00:25:01.202
-Hey. I'll give you
a ride home. all right?
-Please.

468
00:25:02.136 --> 00:25:03.337
Don't follow me!

469
00:25:03.471 --> 00:25:05.006
See what you did?

470
00:25:05.906 --> 00:25:06.841
Oh. I got to take this.

471
00:25:06.974 --> 00:25:08.075
What?

472
00:25:08.209 --> 00:25:10.478
Hi. Cynthia.
Thank you for calling me back.

473
00:25:11.078 --> 00:25:14.548
Yeah. I know. little Hudson.

474
00:25:14.682 --> 00:25:16.851
I know he's still
a little afraid of the ball.
but it's okay.

475
00:25:16.984 --> 00:25:18.986
It's perfectly natural.

476
00:25:19.120 --> 00:25:21.856
We're gonna help him
find his guts. He's gonna
make a great shortstop--

477
00:25:24.458 --> 00:25:25.626
Oh.

478
00:25:25.760 --> 00:25:27.695
Holy hell! Will!

479
00:25:27.828 --> 00:25:29.897
Cynthia. I gotta call you back.

480
00:25:32.833 --> 00:25:34.068
What was that for?

481
00:25:34.201 --> 00:25:36.337
I-I don't know.
I apologize. Um...

482
00:25:36.470 --> 00:25:37.972
Now I gotta call Cynthia back!

483
00:25:38.105 --> 00:25:40.207
Yeah. no. of course.
Go-Go ahead.

484
00:25:40.341 --> 00:25:43.577
Her son's had
a really hard year.
His dog died.

485
00:25:45.179 --> 00:25:46.614
Hudson can go to hell!

486
00:26:15.276 --> 00:26:16.811
Hey. hey! Break it up!

487
00:26:16.944 --> 00:26:18.145
-Georgia Bureau
of Investigation!
-County Sheriff's Department!

488
00:26:18.279 --> 00:26:19.613
Back off!

489
00:26:19.747 --> 00:26:20.981
Okay.

490
00:26:28.557 --> 00:26:30.658
What is your problem?

491
00:26:30.791 --> 00:26:34.829
You are my problem.
Okay? You and your stupid
Little League team.

492
00:26:34.962 --> 00:26:38.365
You're mad at me because
I'm coaching Little League?

493
00:26:38.499 --> 00:26:40.367
I'm mad
because you didn't coach me.

494
00:26:46.541 --> 00:26:51.479
I was this little kid
getting kicked around
in a dozen different homes.

495
00:26:51.612 --> 00:26:54.715
- All the while. you were. what?
- Living in your big house.

496
00:26:55.749 --> 00:26:59.053
With your Little League team
and your whipped cream
and your sprinkles.

497
00:26:59.687 --> 00:27:02.256
-I didn't know you existed!
-Well. you should've!

498
00:27:02.790 --> 00:27:03.991
Well. I didn't!

499
00:27:04.725 --> 00:27:06.660
And by the way.
you gotta step into it.

500
00:27:06.794 --> 00:27:08.462
A little too much sidearm.
Here. try again.

501
00:27:20.609 --> 00:27:22.643
Ow.

502
00:27:24.613 --> 00:27:25.646
You okay?

503
00:27:27.448 --> 00:27:29.350
Yeah. I mean.
you barely touched me.

504
00:27:31.152 --> 00:27:33.622
-You?
-Same. Totally fine.

505
00:27:35.990 --> 00:27:39.393
I'm sorry I hit you.
You don't have to forgive me.

506
00:27:39.528 --> 00:27:40.995
I forgive you.

507
00:27:42.631 --> 00:27:47.468
I get it. I hope one day
you'll be able to forgive me.

508
00:27:51.372 --> 00:27:53.542
Should we go back
to talking about the case?

509
00:27:54.675 --> 00:27:57.144
It's probably safer. yes.

510
00:28:04.351 --> 00:28:07.188
Viktor said he was carrying
two film cases to the office.

511
00:28:07.321 --> 00:28:08.523
Yeah.

512
00:28:08.657 --> 00:28:10.024
When we went to
the projection booth...

513
00:28:10.157 --> 00:28:11.358
There were three cases
in there.

514
00:28:11.492 --> 00:28:14.563
Exactly.
Think that's something?

515
00:28:14.695 --> 00:28:15.963
Could be.

516
00:28:17.431 --> 00:28:18.465
Good talk.

517
00:28:22.836 --> 00:28:24.606
You get that thing
open already?

518
00:28:25.339 --> 00:28:28.175
There's a thousand
keys here. Polaski.
I'm trying the best I can.

519
00:28:29.644 --> 00:28:31.546
I've just gotta pee.

520
00:28:31.680 --> 00:28:35.082
Again? You know.
it's starting to feel like
dereliction of duty.

521
00:28:35.216 --> 00:28:37.751
the amount you pee these days.

522
00:28:37.885 --> 00:28:40.087
Yeah. right. Pretend you know
what dereliction means.

523
00:28:41.021 --> 00:28:45.527
Oh. sure. make fun of Ormy.
Everyone loves to make fun
of Ormy.

524
00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:49.897
Ormy saves the day.
once again.

525
00:28:56.571 --> 00:28:57.706
Whoa.

526
00:29:14.556 --> 00:29:17.692
Hey! Who the hell are you?

527
00:29:17.825 --> 00:29:21.895
Oh. um. I'm just in the market
for a new TV. You got any?

528
00:29:23.897 --> 00:29:25.065
Whoa!

529
00:29:25.199 --> 00:29:26.267
Hey!

530
00:29:28.536 --> 00:29:29.571
Stop!

531
00:29:38.312 --> 00:29:40.447
Hey! I said stop!

532
00:29:45.886 --> 00:29:47.589
Say derelict again. I dare you.

533
00:29:48.922 --> 00:29:51.425
Ormewood
does not save the day.

534
00:29:51.559 --> 00:29:52.594
You wanna cuff him?

535
00:29:58.432 --> 00:29:59.466
Gotta pee again.

536
00:30:00.535 --> 00:30:01.670
God!

537
00:30:04.805 --> 00:30:06.140
There's the third film reel.

538
00:30:10.612 --> 00:30:16.350
Okay. so if you aren't
the movie Viktor was screening.
then what are you?

539
00:30:24.158 --> 00:30:25.326
Oh.

540
00:30:25.459 --> 00:30:27.961
-Look at this.
-Is that Avery?

541
00:30:28.697 --> 00:30:30.064
Yeah.

542
00:30:34.301 --> 00:30:36.036
-Oh. my God.
-Yeah.

543
00:30:36.170 --> 00:30:37.471
-It's--
-But what about--

544
00:30:37.605 --> 00:30:38.839
You go.

545
00:30:38.972 --> 00:30:40.508
And you stay. in case--

546
00:30:40.642 --> 00:30:41.676
Yep.

547
00:30:46.648 --> 00:30:49.016
Viktor! Viktor!

548
00:30:52.486 --> 00:30:54.589
Viktor! Viktor!

549
00:30:55.422 --> 00:30:57.224
-Viktor.
-Sheriff!

550
00:30:57.358 --> 00:31:00.327
Gotta find Viktor Langley.
Last seen in the company
of Avery's suspected murderer.

551
00:31:00.461 --> 00:31:03.063
Ah. No way. You're saying
the vampire didn't do it?

552
00:31:03.197 --> 00:31:04.198
Doesn't look like it.

553
00:31:04.865 --> 00:31:06.701
Viktor. Oh. my God.

554
00:31:07.769 --> 00:31:08.803
Oh. my God.

555
00:31:09.436 --> 00:31:10.437
Viktor!

556
00:31:13.675 --> 00:31:17.044
Faint pulse. Pinpoint pupils.

557
00:31:18.045 --> 00:31:20.381
Oh. Fentanyl. He's overdosing.

558
00:31:20.515 --> 00:31:23.217
Kenny. there's Narcan
in the truck. Go get it now.

559
00:31:25.185 --> 00:31:27.221
Come on. kid.
Come on. stay with me.

560
00:31:28.055 --> 00:31:29.724
Okay. you want me to say it?
I'm gonna say it.

561
00:31:30.324 --> 00:31:33.528
Are you hearing me?
You're a vampire. okay?

562
00:31:33.661 --> 00:31:38.465
You're a vampire!
You cannot die!
You will not die. okay?

563
00:31:39.066 --> 00:31:40.934
Viktor. Viktor!

564
00:31:46.173 --> 00:31:50.545
I'm not losing you. kid.
Come on. I need you
to get back in the game!

565
00:31:54.148 --> 00:31:55.750
I-It was Landon.

566
00:32:45.667 --> 00:32:46.868
<i>Landon.</i>

567
00:32:51.171 --> 00:32:53.307
You worked concessions
with Avery.

568
00:32:55.610 --> 00:32:56.977
You were obsessed with her.

569
00:32:58.580 --> 00:33:00.682
You didn't know
how to tell her.
so you made this movie.

570
00:33:00.815 --> 00:33:03.116
Did you show it to her. Landon?

571
00:33:03.250 --> 00:33:05.052
She was my muse.

572
00:33:05.954 --> 00:33:07.454
Yeah. but she didn't wanna be.

573
00:33:08.790 --> 00:33:11.860
I made something beautiful
for her. because of her.

574
00:33:11.992 --> 00:33:14.596
and she said that it was weird
and creepy.

575
00:33:14.729 --> 00:33:18.465
and that she didn't want...
work the same shift
as me anymore.

576
00:33:18.600 --> 00:33:20.467
She rejected you.

577
00:33:21.034 --> 00:33:24.506
So you killed her
and framed your coworker.

578
00:33:25.573 --> 00:33:27.809
I could have made her
a movie star.

579
00:33:34.314 --> 00:33:36.918
Come on. You're under arrest.
Let's go.

580
00:33:38.653 --> 00:33:39.888
Come on.

581
00:34:02.677 --> 00:34:03.711
Hey.

582
00:34:04.478 --> 00:34:08.315
Hey. just. uh. came by
to check in on you.

583
00:34:08.448 --> 00:34:09.851
It's good
to see you feeling better.

584
00:34:10.484 --> 00:34:11.519
Yeah.

585
00:34:12.620 --> 00:34:13.655
Oh.

586
00:34:14.722 --> 00:34:17.792
Uh. I have to say.
I miss the fangs.

587
00:34:17.926 --> 00:34:20.260
Yeah. me too.

588
00:34:21.161 --> 00:34:23.463
But they made it really hard
to eat a sandwich.

589
00:34:25.098 --> 00:34:27.367
-Yeah.
-I'm cutting back on some
of the vampire stuff.

590
00:34:27.501 --> 00:34:29.436
I think I will keep the coffin.
though.

591
00:34:32.172 --> 00:34:35.577
You know. what's the deal
with the coffin anyway?

592
00:34:37.011 --> 00:34:38.746
When I was a kid.
I was scared of the dark.

593
00:34:39.413 --> 00:34:42.684
And sometimes at night.
I used to climb into bed
with my parents.

594
00:34:44.052 --> 00:34:47.622
Once they were gone.
I had to figure out how to deal
with the darkness myself.

595
00:34:47.755 --> 00:34:49.289
You became a vampire.

596
00:34:50.457 --> 00:34:54.963
Once I explored the darkness.
it wasn't so scary anymore.

597
00:34:55.095 --> 00:34:57.999
Mmm. Exploring the darkness.

598
00:34:58.465 --> 00:35:01.002
Sounds dangerous.

599
00:35:01.769 --> 00:35:02.804
It doesn't have to be.

600
00:35:07.909 --> 00:35:08.943
Uh...

601
00:35:12.780 --> 00:35:15.282
Hey. uh. your father's here.
You want me to go talk to him?

602
00:35:15.415 --> 00:35:16.985
Oh. no. I called him.

603
00:35:17.117 --> 00:35:18.720
-You did?
-Yeah.

604
00:35:18.853 --> 00:35:21.956
After Landon
put those patches on me.
I started losing consciousness.

605
00:35:22.090 --> 00:35:23.625
And my last thought was.

606
00:35:23.758 --> 00:35:26.828
"I can't believe
I'm going to die
before I talk to my dad again."

607
00:35:30.765 --> 00:35:35.970
That's. uh...
it's very brave of you. Viktor.

608
00:35:36.771 --> 00:35:39.306
Thanks. I'll see you.

609
00:36:57.350 --> 00:36:59.721
I love
all my kids unconditionally.

610
00:37:00.722 --> 00:37:02.857
but I can't always say
I understand them.

611
00:37:04.726 --> 00:37:06.027
What you doing?

612
00:37:07.394 --> 00:37:08.563
I'm. uh...

613
00:37:10.230 --> 00:37:11.733
exploring the darkness.

614
00:37:13.835 --> 00:37:15.169
I can see that.

615
00:37:23.243 --> 00:37:25.947
I've been doing that lately.

616
00:37:26.080 --> 00:37:28.816
-How's that going?
-Mixed.

617
00:37:30.685 --> 00:37:32.153
I lost my temper earlier.

618
00:37:34.454 --> 00:37:35.890
It's been happening a lot.

619
00:37:38.092 --> 00:37:39.861
It's not fair to you.

620
00:37:40.862 --> 00:37:41.896
Will. I get it.

621
00:37:43.831 --> 00:37:47.935
The fact that I had a son
out there in the world
that I didn't know about.

622
00:37:48.069 --> 00:37:50.370
who went through
what you went through...

623
00:37:50.505 --> 00:37:52.974
it's the tragedy of my life.

624
00:37:54.374 --> 00:37:55.977
You know. in a weird way...

625
00:37:58.112 --> 00:38:01.816
it was easier when
I didn't know I had a father.

626
00:38:02.415 --> 00:38:05.620
I had accepted that.
But now you're here.

627
00:38:08.122 --> 00:38:10.992
And all I see
is everything I missed out on.

628
00:38:17.265 --> 00:38:20.735
It's hard not to be angry.

629
00:38:22.570 --> 00:38:25.506
I'm sorry I wasn't there.
but I'm here now.

630
00:38:40.822 --> 00:38:42.355
Help me get out of here.
will you?

631
00:38:48.963 --> 00:38:50.430
Mike called.

632
00:38:50.565 --> 00:38:53.167
Your car's ready.
and you're right.
it was a carburetor.

633
00:38:53.835 --> 00:38:56.137
Let's get you over there
so you can pick up your car.

634
00:38:56.270 --> 00:38:57.805
and you can get out
of this town.

635
00:38:58.371 --> 00:39:02.877
Hey. um. what about that dinner
you still owe me?

636
00:39:06.781 --> 00:39:09.150
Great. Let's eat.

637
00:39:17.758 --> 00:39:19.327
Heard you caught
the second guy.

638
00:39:20.261 --> 00:39:21.361
We got him.

639
00:39:21.494 --> 00:39:22.763
Thank you.

640
00:39:23.931 --> 00:39:27.635
It was. uh. a relief
to hear he was in custody.

641
00:39:29.369 --> 00:39:30.905
Yeah. it was.

642
00:39:36.677 --> 00:39:37.678
You wanna sit?

643
00:39:49.023 --> 00:39:52.059
You... you saw some action
in Afghanistan. right?

644
00:39:52.660 --> 00:39:53.728
I did. yeah.

645
00:39:55.395 --> 00:39:56.998
Wait. but how did you...

646
00:40:01.035 --> 00:40:03.204
When you got back. Did...

647
00:40:03.905 --> 00:40:06.974
Well. at first.
I couldn't talk about it.

648
00:40:07.575 --> 00:40:09.442
I didn't want to relive it.
so I ignored it.

649
00:40:09.577 --> 00:40:11.712
And all that did
was make me angry.

650
00:40:13.413 --> 00:40:17.218
You know. I got to the point
where I'd look in the mirror.

651
00:40:17.351 --> 00:40:19.419
and I didn't know
who the hell I was looking at.

652
00:40:22.256 --> 00:40:24.759
And then Gina...

653
00:40:24.892 --> 00:40:29.363
...she found a meeting that
I could go to. and that helped.

654
00:40:31.132 --> 00:40:34.769
I actually think if I'd have
gone earlier. my marriage
might have been better.

655
00:40:35.803 --> 00:40:38.471
Might not have done
some of the things
I'm ashamed of now.

656
00:40:41.976 --> 00:40:44.745
Yeah. talking helps.

657
00:40:56.390 --> 00:40:58.659
When that man
had his gun to my head.

658
00:40:59.927 --> 00:41:01.829
I knew I was dead.

659
00:41:03.931 --> 00:41:04.999
I froze.

660
00:41:06.133 --> 00:41:07.435
In that moment...

661
00:41:10.237 --> 00:41:11.272
I froze.

662
00:41:14.108 --> 00:41:16.510
And it got me killed.

663
00:41:17.778 --> 00:41:19.914
But that's not what happened.
is it?

664
00:41:20.982 --> 00:41:22.016
No.

665
00:41:22.883 --> 00:41:23.918
What happened?

666
00:41:26.220 --> 00:41:27.588
Say it.

667
00:41:28.289 --> 00:41:29.489
A child appeared.

668
00:41:30.458 --> 00:41:33.361
That's right. And then what?

669
00:41:36.330 --> 00:41:38.132
I protected her.

670
00:41:40.334 --> 00:41:41.535
No one else died.

671
00:41:44.438 --> 00:41:45.539
And what happened to you?

672
00:41:47.708 --> 00:41:49.143
I lived.

673
00:41:54.015 --> 00:41:56.117
I lived.

673
00:41:57.305 --> 00:42:57.864
